              vqaqpepm0xbba9pwe9Q8fs0=yqaqpepae9pg0FirpepeKkFr0xfr=x
              fr=xb9adbaqaaeGaciGaaiaabeqaamaabaabaaGcbaaeaaaaaaaaa8
              qacaWGfbWaamWaaeaacqaH4oqCcaGG8bGaamiraaGaay5waiaaw2fa
              aiabg2da9iabgUIiYlabeI7aXjaadchadaqadaqaaiabeI7aXjaacY
              hacaWGebaacaGLOaGaayzkaaGaamizaiabeI7aXbaa@4974@ </annotation>
          </semantics>
        </math>
      </equation>

      <para>The term <inlineequation>
          <m:math display="inline">
            <m:mrow>
              <m:msub>
                <m:mi>q</m:mi>

                <m:mi>Y</m:mi>
              </m:msub>

              <m:mo>[E(θ|D)]</m:mo>
            </m:mrow>
          </m:math>
        </inlineequation> is referred to as the expected parameter X% AEP
      quantile. When this term is used it is understood that the quantile is
      computed with <inlineequation>
          <m:math display="inline">
            <m:mi>θ</m:mi>
          </m:math>
        </inlineequation> assigned <inlineequation>
          <m:math display="inline">
            <m:mi>[E(θ|D)]</m:mi>
          </m:math>
        </inlineequation>.</para>
    </section>

    <section xml:id="b3_ch2_s_97ehe">
      <title>Linear asymmetric loss</title>

      <para>The linear asymmetric loss function may be appropriate when the consequences of
        under<?oxy_delete author="RadhikaChhotai" timestamp="20151022T162525+1100" content="-"?> and
        over<?oxy_insert_start author="RadhikaChhotai" timestamp="20151022T162529+1100"?>-<?oxy_insert_end?>design
        are judged to be different. The loss function is expressed as:</para>

      <equation xml:id="b3_ch2_e_ggb3h">
        <math display="block" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
          <semantics>
            <mrow>
              <mtext>L</mtext>
              <mrow>
                <mo>[</mo>
                <mrow>
                  <msub>
                    <mtext>q</mtext>
                    <mi>Y</mi>
                  </msub>
                  <mrow>
                    <mo>(</mo>
                    <mtext>D</mtext>
                    <mo>)</mo>
                  </mrow>
                  <msub>
                    <mrow>
                      <mtext>,q</mtext>
                    </mrow>
                    <mi>Y</mi>
                  </msub>
                  <mrow>
                    <mo>(</mo>
                    <mi>&#x03B8;</mi>
                    <mo>)</mo>
                  </mrow>
                </mrow>
                <mo>]</mo>
              </mrow>
              <mtext>&#x2009;</mtext>
              <mtext>&#x2009;</mtext>
              <mo>=</mo>
              <mrow>
                <mo>{</mo>
                <mrow>
                  <mtable columnalign="left">
                    <mtr columnalign="left">
                      <mtd columnalign="left">
                        <mrow>
                          <mi>&#x03B1;</mi>
                          <mrow>
                            <mo>(</mo>
                            <mrow>
                              <msub>
                                <mtext>q</mtext>
                                <mi>Y</mi>
                              </msub>
                              <mtext>(&#x03B8;</mtext>
                              <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
                              <mo>&#x2212;</mo>
                              <msub>
                                <mtext>q</mtext>
                                <mi>Y</mi>
                              </msub>
                              <mrow>
                                <mo>(</mo>
                                <mtext>D</mtext>
                                <mo>)</mo>
                              </mrow>
                            </mrow>
                            <mo>)</mo>
                          </mrow>
                          <mtext>&#x2009;</mtext>
                          <mtext>&#x2009;</mtext>
                          <mtext>&#x2009;</mtext>
                          <mtext>if</mtext>
                          <mtext>&#x2009;</mtext>
                          <msub>
                            <mtext>q</mtext>
                            <mi>Y</mi>
