  <section xml:id="b3_ch2_s_up1rb">
    <title>Selection of Flood Quantile Estimator</title>

    <para>The choice of flood quantile estimator depends on whether the design is being carried out
      for many sites or a single site, on whether risk, actual discharge or average annual damage is
      of primary interest in design and on whether the consequences of
      under<?oxy_delete author="RadhikaChhotai" timestamp="20151022T162738+1100" content="-"?> and
      over<?oxy_insert_start author="RadhikaChhotai" timestamp="20151022T162742+1100"?>-<?oxy_insert_end?>design
      are different. The choice is somewhat subjective and may be a matter of policy. As a general
      guide, a non-exhaustive list of recommendations is given below:</para>

    <orderedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>In situations where there is indifference to the consequences of
          under<?oxy_delete author="RadhikaChhotai" timestamp="20151022T162754+1100" content="-"?>
          or
          over<?oxy_insert_start author="RadhikaChhotai" timestamp="20151022T162757+1100"?>-<?oxy_insert_end?>design,
          either the expected parameter or expected AEP quantile can be chosen.</para>

        <para>Expected parameter quantiles should be considered where:</para>

        <orderedlist numeration="lowerroman">
          <listitem>
            <para>Sizing of a structure is of primary interest rather than actual frequency of
              flooding, such as some bridges, culverts or drainage
              pipes<?oxy_insert_start author="RadhikaChhotai" timestamp="20151022T162817+1100"?>;<?oxy_insert_end?></para>
          </listitem>

          <listitem>
            <para>Design is carried out to an arbitrary standard<?oxy_insert_start author="RadhikaChhotai" timestamp="20151022T162827+1100"?>,<?oxy_insert_end?>
              <?oxy_delete author="RadhikaChhotai" timestamp="20151022T162831+1100" content="which has been "?>judged
              to be satisfactory on the basis of experience from previous practice. Many of the
              design standards in ARR 1987<?oxy_insert_start author="RadhikaChhotai" timestamp="20151022T162842+1100"?>,<?oxy_insert_end?>
              <?oxy_comment_start author="RadhikaChhotai" timestamp="20151022T162856+1100" comment="Does this have a link?"?>Book
              3 Sections 1.8 and 1.9<?oxy_comment_end?>, fall into this
              category<?oxy_insert_start author="RadhikaChhotai" timestamp="20151022T162906+1100"?>;
              and<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="RadhikaChhotai" timestamp="20151022T162906+1100" content="."?></para>
          </listitem>

          <listitem>
            <para>Unbiased estimates of annual flood damages are required
            (Doran and Irish, 1980).</para>
          </listitem>
        </orderedlist>

        <para>Expected AEP quantiles should be considered where:</para>

        <orderedlist numeration="lowerroman">
          <listitem>
            <para>Design is required for many sites in a region, and the objective is to attain a
              desired AEP over all
              sites<?oxy_insert_start author="RadhikaChhotai" timestamp="20151022T162913+1100"?>;<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="RadhikaChhotai" timestamp="20151022T162913+1100" content="."?></para>
          </listitem>

          <listitem>
            <para>Flood estimates are made at multiple sites with different record
              lengths<?oxy_delete author="RadhikaChhotai" timestamp="20151022T162920+1100" content=","?>
              and a comparable basis is required for flood estimates of a given
              AEP<?oxy_insert_start author="RadhikaChhotai" timestamp="20151022T162928+1100"?>;<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="RadhikaChhotai" timestamp="20151022T162925+1100" content="."?></para>
          </listitem>

          <listitem>
            <para>Risk or frequency of exceedance is of primary importance for design at a single
              site (such as in floodplain
              management)<?oxy_insert_start author="RadhikaChhotai" timestamp="20151022T162934+1100"?>;
              and<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="RadhikaChhotai" timestamp="20151022T162933+1100" content="."?></para>
          </listitem>

          <listitem>
            <para>Split sample testing of flood estimation procedures (Beard,
            1960).</para>
          </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>If there are significant differences between the consequences of
          under<?oxy_delete author="RadhikaChhotai" timestamp="20151022T162804+1100" content="-"?>
          and
          over<?oxy_insert_start author="RadhikaChhotai" timestamp="20151022T162808+1100"?>-<?oxy_insert_end?>design,
          consideration should be given to using <xref linkend="b3_ch2_e_xmck8"/> as the flood
          quantile estimator.</para>
      </listitem>
    </orderedlist>
  </section>
